message_1:
What is the median of the following data set:

15, 22, 18, 16, 21, 20, 19, 23, 17, 19.
message_2:
To find the median of this data set, we first need to arrange the numbers in ascending order:

15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23

Since there are 10 numbers in the data set (an even number), the median will be the average of the two middle numbers (the 5th and 6th numbers in this case):

(19 + 19) / 2 = 38 / 2 = 19

The median of this data set is 19.
